1.name: Newspaper and Flyers
1.description: Daily and community newspapers and advertising flyers
1.not_include: Plastic bags used to cover newspaper/flyers (take to Recycle BC recycling depot), rubber Bands

2.name: Magazines and Catalogues
2.description: All types of magazines and catalogues

3.name: Telephone Books
3.not_include: Hardcover or paperback books (donate or sell)

4.name: Writing paper and correspondence
4.description: Note pads; loose leaf paper; white or coloured computer copier and printer paper; printed paper; plain and window envelopes; shredded paper

5.name: Corrugated Cardboard Boxes
5.description:
Shipping boxes, grocery and liquor store boxes, pizza boxes
Empty Boxes: Flatten large corrugated boxes and cut down to no larger than 30 wide (78 cm) X 30 tall (78 cm), staples and tape OK
5.not_include: Cardboard boxes with wax coating, e.g. empty shipping boxes made available for residents to transport their groceries home

6.name: Cardboard/boxboard
6.description:
Boxes for cereal, shoes, tissues, pizza, frozen entrees, desserts, detergent, etc. Carrier trays for bulk bottled water, soft drinks, cans, food, etc.
Cores for paper towel and toilet tissue Flatten and place boxboard directly into the collection container, not inside another box
Remove liner bags and food residue
6.not_include: Paper towels or napkins (include with green waste, if applicable, tissues

7.name: Moulded boxboard packaging
7.description: Egg cartons, take-out beverage trays, empty paper-based garden pots, etc

8.name: Paper Bags (kraft paper)
8.description: Any colour, including brown grocery sacks, white prescription bags, brown envelopes
8.not_include: Padded envelopes, foil-lined bags (e.g., packaged cookies)

9.name: Multi-layer paper bags
9.description: Multi-layered paper bags for flour, sugar, etc.
9.not_include: Bags with a foil layer, bags with a plastic layer

10.name: Paper Cups
10.description:
For hot and cold beverages
 Empty and rinse cups
 Remove lids and place loose with
container recycling
 Recycle paper sleeves separately

11.name: Gable-top cartons
11.description:
For milk, milk-type beverages, cream, substitute eggs, sugar, molasses, etc.
 Empty and rinse cartons
 If carton includes plastic screw
cap, remove cap and place loose in recycling container
11.not_include: Paper towels or napkins (include with green waste, if applicable, tissues

12.name: Aseptic boxes or cartons
12.description:
For milk, milk-type beverages, cream, soup, broth, sauces, etc.
 Add loose to recycling container
12.not_include: Juice cartons (return for deposit refund), straws, stand-up pouches

13.name: Frozen dessert boxes
13.description: For ice cream, frozen yogurt, etc.  Empty and rinse cartons

14.name: Empty Aerosol Containers
14.description:
For food, air fresheners, shaving cream, deodorant, hairspray, etc.
 Empty cans
 Remove caps and place loose in
recycling container
14.not_include: Spray paint cans, erosol cans with any contents remaining, propane cylinders

15.name: Spiral Wound Cans and Metal Lids
15.description:
For frozen juice concentrate, potato chips, cookie dough, coffee, nuts, baby formula, etc.
 Remove lids and place loose in recycling container
15.not_include: Paper towels or napkins (include with green waste, if applicable, tissues

16.name: Steel Cans and Lids
16.description:
For food including pet food; tins for cookies, tea, chocolates, etc.; include metal lid
 Empty and rinse cans
 Labels OK
 Put metal lid inside can and
squeeze slightly
16.not_include:
Steel beverage cans (return
for deposit refund), steel paint cans, coat hangers (return to dry cleaners), pots, pans and baking trays, propane cylinders, metal toys, appliances, metal hardware or other scrap metal, wiring or metal cords, extension cords

17.name: Alunimum Cans and Lids
17.description:
For food, e.g. seafood, cat food, etc.
 Empty and rinse cans
 Labels OK
 Put metal lid inside can and
squeeze slightly
17.not_include: Propane tanks or propane canisters, deposit cans (return for deposit refund)

18.name: Aluminum Foil and Foil Take-Out Containers
18.description:
Foil wrap and take-out containers including pie plates, food trays, etc.
 Empty and rinse containers
18.not_include:
Chip or foil bags, foil wrap
with paper backing for butter, cigarettes, etc., foil-lined cardboard take-out containers or lids

19.name: Plastic Jugs with Screw Tops
19.description:
For milk, cooking oil, laundry detergent, fabric softener, cleaning solutions, cleaning products, body care products, windshield washer fluid, etc.
 Empty and rinse jugs
 Labels OK
19.not_include: Jugs for flavoured tea, juice, other beverages (return for deposit refund)

20.name: Plastic Clamshells
20.description:
For baked goods, fruit, produce, eggs, etc. Containers are clear with hinged or click-closed tops.
 Empty and rinse containers
 Labels OK
20.not_include: Packaging labelled biodegradable or compostable, liquid-absorbing pads

21.name: Plastic Jars and Lids
21.description:
For peanut butter, jam, nuts, condiments, vitamins and supplements, personal care products and cosmetics, pharmaceuticals, etc.
 Plastic jars have wide mouths with screw-top lids
 Empty and rinse jars
 Labels OK
 Remove lids and place loose in
recycling container
21.not_include: Beverage bottles (return for deposit refund), stand-up pouches, containers for motor oil, vehicle lubricant, or antifreeze products

22.name: Plastic Bottles and Caps
22.description:
For food, dish soap, mouthwash, shampoos, conditioners and other personal care products, pills and vitamins, laundry products, household cleaners, automotive cleaners, e.g., glass cleaner, windshield washer fluid, etc.
 Plastic bottles have screw caps, spray pump or pull-up tops
 Empty and rinse bottles
 Labels OK
 Remove caps, spray pump and
pull-up tops, and place loose in recycling container
22.not_include: Beverage bottles (return for deposit refund), stand-up pouches, containers for motor oil, vehicle lubricant, or antifreeze products
